            "content": "## TUI Improvements\n\nRatatui best practices adoption based on ecosystem analysis of awesome-ratatui libraries and reference apps (tgt, iamb, nostui, mqttui, twitch-tui). Recommended between v0.5 and v0.6.\n\n---\n\n### Current baseline problems\n\n- **Blocking I/O in async**: `event.rs` uses `crossterm::event::poll()` (blocking syscall) inside `tokio::spawn`, tying up a worker thread for 100ms per iteration\n- **Wasted draws**: `terminal.draw()` runs on every `select!` wakeup, including no-op `Tick` events (10 draws/sec when idle)\n- **Broken list highlight**: Conversation list uses `render_widget` without `ListState` — `highlight_style` is dead code, selection can scroll off-screen\n- **Layout index bugs**: `ui.rs` has 7+ `chunks[N]` index accesses — wrong index = silent rendering bug\n- **Popup boilerplate**: 4 popups with duplicated rendering (manual `Clear` + rect math) and 4 separate `show_*_popup` bools with sequential `if` dispatch\n- **Monolithic App**: `app.rs` is 1560+ lines with `#[allow(clippy::too_many_lines)]` on `update()` and `handle_key_event()`\n- **Scattered spawns**: `tokio::spawn` + `action_tx.clone()` pattern repeated inline for every async operation\n\n### Reference patterns\n\n| Pattern | Source app | What reme adopts |\n|---------|-----------|-----------------|\n| `EventStream` async input | twitch-tui | Replace blocking `event::poll` |\n| `needs_render` atomic flag | tgt | Skip draws on idle ticks |\n| `ListState` on all lists | tgt, nostui, rvIRC, iamb | Fix conversation list highlight |\n| `PopupKind` enum | ratatui-interact (internalized) | Replace `show_*` bools |\n| `Component` trait | tgt | Decompose monolithic App |\n| `Requester` / typed handle | iamb | Wrap `action_tx` in typed methods |\n\n### New dependencies\n\n| Crate | Trust | Purpose |\n|-------|-------|---------|\n| `ratatui-macros` | First-party ratatui-org | Eliminate `chunks[N]` index bugs via `vertical![==1, ==3].areas()` |\n| `tui-popup` | josh